2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
¾ cup Basmati Rice
113 g Baby Tomatoes
56 g Carrot, julienned
56 g Green Peas
113 g Onion, sliced
3 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
2 tbsp Curry Paste
1 tbsp Vegetable Stock Powder
1.5 tsp Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
¼ tsp Salt*
1 tsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
¼ tsp Pepper*

Once water is boiling, add rice, carrots, vegetable stock powder, half the Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter.
Stir to mix, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Halve tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and half the yogurt sauce to a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to coat.

Heat a large non-stick pan over high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties, onions and peas.
Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Reduce heat to medium. Add curry paste, broth concentrate, remaining Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar and 1/3 cup (2/3 cup) water.
Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with fork.
Divide rice, Beyond Meat® and creamy tomatoes between plates.
Drizzle remaining yogurt sauce over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the beef, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**